n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post__text\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"post__meta\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a data-lpos=\"inline-recirc-module\" data-lid=\"Washington DC\" class=\"post__tag\" href=\"https:\/\/www.nbcwashington.com\/tag\/washington-dc\/\">Washington DC<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"post__date post__date--has-category\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<time class=\"entry-date published\" datetime=\"2025-03-28T16:08:26+00:00\">Mar 28<\/time>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<h3 class=\"post__title\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<a data-lpos=\"inline-recirc-module\" data-lid=\"Trump says House should \u2018immediately&#039; pass DC budget fix\" class=\"post__title--link\" href=\"https:\/\/www.nbcwashington.com\/news\/local\/trump-says-house-should-pass-dc-budget-fix-immediately\/3878685\/\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tTrump says House should \u2018immediately&#039; pass DC budget fix\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/a>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/h3>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t"},{"blockName":"core\/paragraph","attrs":[],"namespace":"core","rendered":"\n<p>\u201cWe are talking about serious and significant cuts to city operations, public safety, public education, our own transit system,\u201d Councilmember Charles Allen said. \u201cSo, it's deeply devastating, and the clock is ticking. The city will have to start moving forward with planning out what those cuts look like that the House is making.\u201d<\/p>\n"},{"blockName":"core\/paragraph","attrs":[],"namespace":"core","rendered":"\n<p>Bowser declined to comment Wednesday, but multiple sources told News4 she and Johnson talked by phone this week to discuss D.C. funding as the House determines a path forward.<\/p>\n"},{"blockName":"core\/paragraph","attrs":[],"namespace":"core","rendered":"\n<p>A spokesperson for Johnson said the speaker has been laser focused on congressional Republicans\u2019 big budget resolution but did not rule out some type of action when the House returns in two weeks.<\/p>\n"},{"blockName":"nbc\/heading","attrs":[],"namespace":"nbc","rendered":"\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-nbc-section-heading\"><em>Get the D.C. area's top news and weather delivered to your inbox every morning. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.nbcwashington.com\/newsletters\/\">Sign up for First &amp; 4Most, our free newsletter.<\/a><\/em><\/h2>\n"}],"nbc_attributes":{"size":"S"},"bylines":[{"description":"<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mark Segraves is a general assignment reporter with News4.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Segraves has been reporting for television, newspaper and radio in the Washington area since 1999. Most recently, he worked at WTOP Radio and WJLA-TV where he specialized in breaking stories involving the D.C. government. He has received many honors for his investigative reporting including Edward R. Murrow Awards, Associated Press Awards and several awards from the Society of Professional Journalists.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Segraves\u2019 journalism career started in Delaware where he worked for both WAFL Radio in Milford and the Coast Press in Rehoboth. His work has also appeared in the Voice of the Hill Newspaper and during newsbreaks on DC-50, Washington\u2019s CW affiliate.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A native of Washington, Segraves grew up in Northwest Washington, close to NBC4\u2019s studios. He attended Gonzaga College High School then the University of Maryland.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->","display_name":"Mark Segraves, News4 Reporter","id":"1:14:2039882","url":"https:\/\/www.nbcwashington.com\/author\/mark-segraves\/","twitter":"SegravesNBC4","twitter_url":"https:\/\/twitter.com\/SegravesNBC4","thumbnail":{"id":5230256,"date":"2020-06-30T13:18:20","title":{"rendered":"2016_Mark_Se